dialogue: Weak. Weak. Weak. Weak. Weak. Weak. Weak. Weak. Weak. Weak.
Surrounded by weaklings. Slobbering, servile, enfeebled, doddering WEAKLINGS.
Do you know what that feels like. WHY! WHY DO I HAVE TO DO EVERYTHING MYSELF!
Most beloved of the Daimaou. Chosen by the Kijohime. I was to inherit this world!
Look at me, monkey! Do I look like a STEPPING STONE!?
Not even a speck of you shall remain.
Yes. It was by her will that I took up the Daimaou's seat.
With her by my side, she'd said, my claim to the throne would be undeniable.
But to think she had a 'champion' this whole time. A monkey like you.
You are the very incarnation of mankind's unsightliness. That is the reason you must perish.
Through death, you will atone for your profanity.
